Let us consider a   system equations : \begin{gather}  
a^3+b=3a+4\tag{i}\\
2b^3+c=6b+6 \tag{ii}\\
3c^3+a=9c+8\tag{iii}
\end{gather} I have tried with the following steps : $6\times(i)+3\times(ii)+2\times$(iii) gives : $6(a^3+b^3+c^3)+6b+3c+2a=18(a+b+c)+58$. But  I don't know how to solve in this way. By inspection method I have seen $a=b=c=2$.
